This paper is about image-to-image translation using GANs, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel training framework for GANs, which involves designing an adjustable objective function and introducing a new adversarial loss and a perceptual-level consistency loss. These aspects of the paper suggest that it could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves working with large-scale datasets, which could make it relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
